JOHANNESBURG - US-based research firm and short-seller, Viceroy, says the South African Reserve Bank’s support for Capitec Bank is based on inaccurate information. The firm has renewed a call for the central bank to carry out a full regulatory inspection on Capitec. READ: Rand stays under pressure as Zuma refuses to go Viceroy’s latest statement follows broad-based local support for the bank after its report said Capitec was reckless with its lending and massively understated defaults. At the same time, Capitec has released a detailed response dismissing Viceroy’s claim that it would need to impair R11-billion in bad loans. The bank provided figures going back to 2015, showing how it calculated its opening and closing gross loans each year.  eNCA